  <title>Test statistic Practice</title>

<introduction>
    <p>
        Let's practice deciding what test statistic to use in different situations!
    </p>
</introduction>


<exercise>

    <statement>
        For each scenario, decide what test statistic to use when doing the hypothesis test.
    </statement>

    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A retailer claims that <m>70\%</m> of customers are satisfied with their service. You want to test this claim using survey data from a random sample of 200 customers.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <choices>

            <choice correct="yes">
                <statement>
                    <p>
	                    <m> z=\frac{\bar{p}-p}{\sqrt{\frac{p\cdot(1-p)}{n}}}</m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </choice>

            <choice>
                <statement>
                    <p>
	                    <m> t=\frac{\bar{x}-\mu}{(s/\sqrt{n})} </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </choice>

            <choice>
                <statement>
                    <p>
	                    <m> z=\frac{\bar{x}-\mu}{(\sigma/\sqrt{n})} </m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </choice>

        </choices>

    </task>




